The paper deals with the problem of semi-supervised learning in relational networks, which involves predicting missing class labels of nodes in a graph-based setting. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with heterogeneity in relational networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. This makes it likely to also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Databases (cs.DB), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
